<h1>CH - Hex to String</h1>

CH(HEX) will convert the sequence of hexadecimal digits into the
corresponding character string. [[CH]] is the inverse of [[HEX]].

<h2>Uses</h2>
<a href="LOGIC.html">LOGIC</a>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<a href="HEX.html">HEX</a>

<<INCLUDES>>=
-INCLUDE 'LOGIC.INC'
@

<<CH>>=
         DEFINE('CH(HEX)T,C,N')                                :(CH_END)
*
CH       HEX LEN(2) . T =                                     :F(RETURN)
         C = HI(T)
         &ALPHABET LEN(C) LEN(1) . C
         CH = CH C                                                 :(CH)
*
CH_END
@

<<unit_test>>=
#!/usr/bin/bash
         exec "snobol4" "-b" "$0" "$@"
-INCLUDE 'CH.INC'
         &CODE = 1
         IDENT(CH('414243'), 'ABC')                              :F(END)
         &CODE = 0
END
@

